==Notable guests==
* On Thursday 29 March 2007, the former [[Taoiseach]] and [[Fianna F<U+00E1>il]] leader [[Bertie Ahern]] briefly visited the school. This followed on from a visit by [[Fine Gael]] leader [[Enda Kenny]] in late 2006.
* On Sunday 8 April 2007, professional golfer [[Paul McGinley]] visited the school to formally launch the Saint Eunan's College Centenary Golf Classic. His father, [[Michael McGinley]] of [[Sigma Wireless Ltd]], is a past student of the College and, having represented the College in the [[MacRory Cup]] final team of 1956, sponsored the prizes for the golf classic.<ref>[http://www.independent.ie/sport/golf/college-backed-by-mcginleys-44076.html Irish Independent - College backed by McGinleys]</ref><ref>DN supplement with local newspaper, dated Friday April 13, 2007, SPORTS page 7</ref>
* On Friday 21 January 2011, [[Labour Party (Ireland)|Labour]] TD [[Pat Rabbitte]] visited the school. He was led around the college by Principal Chris Darby.

